<h1>Where Do Whores Go?</h1>
<br>
<blockquote class="pull-right">
  <p>”<em>Wherever whores go</em>” his father had said. His last words, and what words they were. The crossbow thrummed, Lord Tywin sat back down and Tyrion found himself waddling through the darkness …</p>
  <small>Tywin Lannister, <cite title="Source Title">A Storm of Swords</cite></small>
</blockquote>
<br>
<p class="lead">In his later travels Tyrion Lannister often asked, "<em>Where Do Whores Go?</em>"</p>

<h2 class="lead">Where do whores go?</h2>
<%= form_for @whore, url: whores_path do |f| %>
<%= f.text_field :location, :placeholder => "Whores go...", 
        :class => "input-medium search-query" %>
  <%= f.submit "Answer", :class => "btn" %>
<% end %>

<h4>The last five whores might have gone...</h4>
<% @whores.each do |whore| %>
  <p id="location-<%=whore.id%>" class="well"><%= whore.location %></p>
<% end %>